"Karafyllidis I.","A model for the influence of the greenhouse effect on insect and microorganism geographical distribution and population dynamics",1998,"BioSystems","45","1",,"1","10",,,10.1016/S0303-2647(97)00061-0,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0031982755&partnerID=40&md5=b826c9b9722dd4c46bafcb9439b7f7cb","Dept. of Elec. and Comp. Engineering, Democritus University of Thrace, GR-671 00 Xanthi, Greece","Karafyllidis, I., Dept. of Elec. and Comp. Engineering, Democritus University of Thrace, GR-671 00 Xanthi, Greece","A model for the influence of the greenhouse effect on insect and microorganism geographical distribution and population dynamics using cellular automata is presented. Based on this model, an algorithm has been developed and used to determine the geographical distribution and population dynamics of a hypothetical species in an scenario of global warming. The species' initial population distribution is assumed to be Gaussian. After the initiation of global warming, the population moves and after a few decades the population distribution is no longer Gaussian. Larger populations are found in the direction of population movement.","Cellular automata; Geographical distribution; Global warming; Greenhouse effect; Modelling; Population dynamics","geographical distribution; greenhouse effect; insect; microorganism; modelling; population dynamics; algorithm; article; geographic distribution; greenhouse effect; insect; microorganism; model; nonhuman; population dynamics; Algorithms; Animals; Environmental Microbiology; Greenhouse Effect; Insects; Models, Biological; Population Dynamics; Insecta",,,,,,"Andreadis, I., Karafyllidis, I., Tzionas, P., Thanailakis, A., Tsalides, Ph., A new hardware module for automated visual inspection based on a cellular automaton architecture (1996) J. Intell. Robot. Sys., 16, pp. 89-102; Cubasch, U., Hegerl, G.C., Hellbach, A., Hoeck, H., A climate change simulation starting from 1935 (1995) Clim. Dyn., 11 (2), pp. 71-84; Cunningham, W.P., Saigo, B.W., (1995) Environmental Science, , W.C. Brown, Dubuque, IA; Feynman, R.P., Simulating physics with computers (1982) Int. J. Theor. Phys., 21, pp. 467-488; Gerhard, M., Schuster, H., A cellular automaton describing the formation of spatially ordered structures in chemical systems (1989) Physica. D, 36, pp. 209-221; Gerhard, M., Schuster, H., Tyson, J.J., A cellular automaton model of excitable media (1990) Physica. D, 46, pp. 392-415; Graham, N.E., Simulation of recent global temperature trends (1995) Science, 267 (5198), pp. 666-671; De Groot, W.T., (1992) Environmental Science Theory, , Elsevier, Amsterdam; Karafyllidis, I., Thanailakis, A., Simulation of two-dimensional photoresist etching process in integrated circuit fabrication using cellular automata (1995) Model. Simul. Mater. Sci. Eng., 3, pp. 629-642; Karafyllidis, I., Andreadis, I., Tzionas, P., Tsalides, Ph., Thanailakis, A., A cellular automaton for the determination of the mean velocity of moving objects and its VLSI implementation (1996) Pattern Recognit., 29, pp. 689-699; Klamka, J., Controllability of non-linear models in modelling population dynamics (1994) Appl. Math. Comput. Sci., 4 (2), pp. 203-209; Lischke, H., A Model to Simulate the Population Dynamics of the Codling Moth (Cydiapomonella): Parameter Estimation, Validation and Sensitivity Analysis (1992) Int. Soc. Horticultural Sci., , In: J.G. Buwalda (Ed.) Wageningen, The Netherlands; Mayer, D.G., Atzeni, M.G., Butler, D.G., Adaptation of CLIMEX for spatial screwworm fly population dynamics (1992) Math. Comput. Simul., 33 (5-6), pp. 439-444; Minsky, M., Cellular vacuum (1982) Int. J. Theor. Phys., 21, pp. 537-551; Morse, D.R., (1993) Spatial Simulation Modelling of Insect Population Dynamics on a Transputer Network, , In: Kerridge E.L. (Ed.) IOS Press, Amsterdam; Von Neumann, J., (1966) Theory of Self-Reproducing Automata, , University of Illinois, Urbana, IL; Omohundro, S., Modelling cellular automa